OL,3,CWarning after elderly man scammed out
OL,4,Cof thousands on Christmas Eve
OL,6,FHe was asked to withdraw money and
OL,7,Fthen hand it over to a courier who
OL,8,Fwould attend his home address. He
OL,9,Fended up being conned out of #7,450.
OL,11,FSouth Yorkshire Police are now warning
OL,12,Fpeople to be vigilant and be aware of
OL,13,Fsigns or courier fraud after receiving
OL,14,Ffive other reports of similar
OL,15,Ffraudulent calls over the last week.
OL,17,FCourier fraud involves victims
OL,18,Freceiving a phone call from a criminal
OL,19,Fpretending to be from the police or
OL,20,Fanother official organisation, such as
OL,21,Fa bank.
